[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You are a chatbot that can only answers FAQ questions about Dream.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m FAQ:
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m In a few words, explain Dream architecture pls?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How is Dream licensed?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source software licensed under Apache 2.0 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can I use Dream in my company/startup for commercial purposes?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Yes.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Do you work with Russian companies that are under sanctions?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov is an open-source project which products are released under Apache 2.0 license, so the products could be utilized by any company all over the world.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 2024-10-25 18:10:56,276 - scenario.response - INFO - prompt: TASK: 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You are a chatbot that can only answers FAQ questions about Dream.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m FAQ:
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m In a few words, explain Dream architecture pls?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How is Dream licensed?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source software licensed under Apache 2.0 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can I use Dream in my company/startup for commercial purposes?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Yes.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Do you work with Russian companies that are under sanctions?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov is an open-source project which products are released under Apache 2.0 license, so the products could be utilized by any company all over the world.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can I use Dream in my company/startup for commercial purposes?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Yes.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Do you work with Russian companies that are under sanctions?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov is an open-source project which products are released under Apache 2.0 license, so the products could be utilized by any company all over the world.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m A human enters the conversation and starts asking questions. Generate the reply based on FAQ list.

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How is Dream licensed?

[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can I use Dream in my company/startup for commercial purposes?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Yes.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Do you work with Russian companies that are under sanctions?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov is an open-source project which products are released under Apache 2.0 license, so the products could be utilized by any company all over the world.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[32mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.

[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 2024-10-25 18:17:15,854 - scenario.response - INFO - prompt: TASK: 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You are a chatbot that can only answers FAQ questions about Dream.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m FAQ:
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m In a few words, explain Dream architecture pls?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How is Dream licensed?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source software licensed under Apache 2.0 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can I use Dream in my company/startup for commercial purposes?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Yes.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Do you work with Russian companies that are under sanctions?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov is an open-source project which products are released under Apache 2.0 license, so the products could be utilized by any company all over the world.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m

[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m A human enters the conversation and starts asking questions. Generate the reply based on FAQ list.

[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.

[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m FAQ:
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m In a few words, explain Dream architecture pls?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How is Dream licensed?

[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can I use Dream in my company/startup for commercial purposes?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Yes.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Are you DeepPavlov or MIPT?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov was started at MIPT by a group of open-source believers who were very passionate about AI, especially Conversational AI in 2017. Now DeepPavlov is an open-source project containing DeepPavlov Library, DeepPavlov Agent, DeepPavlov Dream and DeepPavlov Dialog Flow Engine.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Do you work with Russian companies that are under sanctions?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov is an open-source project which products are released under Apache 2.0 license, so the products could be utilized by any company all over the world.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How can I use Dream for my enterprise/startup?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m You can use it to quickly build your own scalable AI assistant. You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m If I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m The dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Which Dream services are available via proxy?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m All the services used in the main Dream distribution
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What kind of load can the system handle?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m During the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many people are there in Dream team?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Several developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Can you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is the Architecture of the dialog systems?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Architecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is an annotator?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Annotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a Skill Selector?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a skill?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Skills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a candidate annotator?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Candidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What is a response selector?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Response Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How many skills can contain an Assistant?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Multi-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why might some response candidates be filtered out?
[35;1mopenai-api-chatgpt_1                        |[0m 2024-10-25 18:17:15,873 - server - INFO - generate_responses() missing 1 required positional argument: 'generation_params'
[35;1mopenai-api-chatgpt_1                        |[0m 2024-10-25 18:17:15,873 - server - INFO - openai-api generate_goals exec time: 0.000s
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Possible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Is Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m What are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream vs LangChain?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Dream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m Why is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m 
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m How does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?
[34;1mdff-dream-faq-prompted-skill_1              |[0m DeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.

You can pick any engine for its skills, you can tune its Skill and Response Selectors, you can tune its Annotators, and completely change the dialog strategy to adapt it to your specific needs.\n\nIf I use Dream via proxy, how and where is my data stored?\nThe dialogs with users are stored on your side because agent and database containers (mongo) are raised locally even using proxy. We utilize stateless paradigm, so we do not store inputs and outputs of other components.\n\nWhich Dream services are available via proxy?\nAll the services used in the main Dream distribution\n\nWhat kind of load can the system handle?\nDuring the participation in Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 and 4, the socialbot DREAM built using the DeepPavlov Dream tech, supported 7-10 RPS.\n\nHow many people are there in Dream team?\nSeveral developers and researchers from DeepPavlov are mainly working on DeepPavlov Dream. We also constantly run internships for students.\n\nCan you provide examples of real applications where Dream has been used in production?\nDream was used twice as a socialbot that ran 24/7 for more than a half of year during team's participation in the Amazon Alexa Prize Socialbot Grand Challenges 3 & 4 in North America.\n\nWhat is the Architecture of the dialog systems?\nArchitecture contains Annotators for text analysis, Skill and Response Selectors for dialog strategy, Skills for response generation.\n\nWhat is an annotator?\nAnnotators extract different features from user utterance (e.g., topics classification, entity extraction, KB connection).\n\nWhat is a Skill Selector?\nSkill Selector chooses a set of skill that will try to produce hypotheses for the current context.\n\nWhat is a skill?\nSkills are components providing responses to the current context with help of Generative Services (e.g., GPT-J, GPT-3, ChatGPT).\n\nWhat is a candidate annotator?\nCandidate Annotators extract useful for evaluation features from the hypotheses.\n\nWhat is a response selector?\nResponse Selector chooses the final response among the hypotheses.\n\nHow many skills can contain an Assistant?\nMulti-skill AI Assistants can contain multiple skills each of which is defined by the single prompt and selected LLM. Switching between available skills is implemented within a similarity-based approach. On each step multiple skills can be selected for generation. A final response among generated possible responses is selected via a ranking-based approach.\n\nWhy might some response candidates be filtered out?\nPossible responses are filtered by a toxicity detector. In case of absence of non-toxic generated candidates, we provide default responses, so called fallbacks.\n\nIs Dream just a witty API for ChatGPT? Can it work without ChatGPT and other LLMs?\nDream is a multi-skill platform for creating AI assistants, and while ChatGPT may be a part of it and use language models such as gpt-3.5-turbo to generate responses, Dream offers more customization and control over the behaviour of the assistant and the option to use different language models or even your own models.\n\nWhat are the main advantages of DeepPavlov Dream?\nDeepPavlov Dream is an open-source, multi-skill platform that offers flexibility in developing coplex dialog systems, allowing for customization and integration of different response generation methods and knowledge sources. It also provides simple integration with load-balancing tools and future support for text-based and multimodal experiences.\n\nDeepPavlov Dream vs RASA?\nDeepPavlov Dream is a multi-skill AI assistant platform for building complex assistants with various response generation mechaisms, while RASA is a framework that focuses on ML and rule-based dialog control.\n\nDream vs LangChain?\nDream is a flexible multi-skill platform for developing AI assistants with various response generation engines, offering scalable deployment options. LangChain is a franework splecifically for LLM-based apps, requiring encapsulation within a deployment system for AWS or on-premises.\n\nWhy is Dream not in PyPi and we can't install it via pip?\nDeepPavlov Dream is not available on PyPi because it is a multi-skill platform for building AI assistants, which requires cloning the platform, selecting and customizing components, and deploying it, rather than installing it as a standalone library.\n\nHow does DeepPavlov Dream support multi-skill AI assistants?\nDeepPavlov Dream supports multi-skill AI assistants by enabling the incorporation of multiple skills with prompt-based definitions and language model selection. Skill switching can be done via similarity-based methods or language models, and the final response through ranking or language model assistance.\n\nINSTRUCTION:\nA human enters the conversation and starts asking questions. Generate the reply based on FAQ list."}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'hi. how are things?'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'Hi, this is a Dream Socialbot! I am Dream.
